Key Match Events: Merih Demiral scored the first goal for Turkey in the very first minute of the game.
Merih Demiral scored a second goal for Turkey just before the hour mark.
Michael Gregoritsch scored a goal for Austria in the 66th minute.
Mert Gunok made a crucial save in the final minute of added time to secure Turkey's victory.
Post-Match Reflections: Turkey's goalkeeper Mert Gunok pulled off what could be the save of the tournament in the final minute of added time.
Turkey will now face the Netherlands in Berlin on Saturday as the final Euro 2024 quarter-final was confirmed.
Turkey are carrying a lot of injuries, suspensions, and potential suspensions into the business end of the tournament, but they also have momentum.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Turkey's goals came from corner kicks, both whipped in by Arda Guler and finished off by Merih Demiral.
Arda Guler orchestrated everything good that Turkey did, calmly kept possession, and drew fouls to alleviate the pressure on his side.
